[LOG] SM_X_JSON:[{"source":"x","url":"https://x.com/prdeepakbabu/status/2018859389139177937","postedAt":"2026-02-04T01:29:21.000Z","text":"I think it is time we start adopting \"skills\". They originated at Anthropic, but now has become an open standard which implies - broader usability across agent platforms including google, openAI and other providers. \"Skills\" are progressively disclosed unlike \"Tools\" which are pre-emptively loaded into context windows taking valuable space that otherwise could make longer conversations possible and more accurate because it avoids context rot.\n\nThe coolest feature I like about skills is availibility of meta-skill called \"skill creator\". Not many realize what skill creator unlocks. I see most people think of this as a UX for creating new skill but what many do not get is it can unlock self-learning (buzz-word now and loosely used incl. here) i.e. you can have agent replay logs overnight, understand commonly used workflows and have the skill creator create new skills automatically and optionally reviewed by humans or judged by LLMs.\n\nIt is ridiculously simple abstraction for lot of things we care about. After careful observations of patterns it is clear - pareto frontier for agents seems to be file systems, web search/browser, coding as tool or model (LLM) together should field 80% of use-cases.","links":["https://t.co/so6VxCwP3E"],"thumbnailUrl":"https://pbs.twimg.com/card_img/2026633779272626180/TAQLqZgn?format=jpg&name=medium","scrapedAt":"2026-03-02T05:15:41.200Z"}] @ :103
